                            <comment id="17180558" author="kinow" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2020 13:39:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds sensible to me. Had a look around to see if I could find anything in the specifications about rounding resolution (which is a LONG), but had no luck.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the sake of being consistent, I think it&apos;s OK that we change, as JpegImageParser is doing it too. Quickly created a BMP in GIMP, with dpi=72.6, reproduced the issue where it was rounded down to 72. Added the suggested `match.round`, and it produced 73.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17180561" author="kinow" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2020 13:43:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;PR created &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rampravin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rampravin&quot;&gt;rampravin&lt;/a&gt; : &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-imaging/pull/94&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-imaging/pull/94&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting the issue!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17180954" author="rampravin" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2020 04:35:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the quick fix &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kinow&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kinow&quot;&gt;kinow&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17180957" author="kinow" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2020 04:44:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t mention it &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rampravin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rampravin&quot;&gt;rampravin&lt;/a&gt; . You did all the hard work of reporting the issue, and you even gave the solution &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; let us know if you find any other issues. Aiming at releasing alpha3 somewhere around the end of the year.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
